@PIN
p001: AXL means squoyster Agent eXecution Language, not Igazine Agent eXchange Language.
p002: Use AXL-R for rules; AXL-S for durable state.
p003: Do not load full AXL spec in routine Hermes startup.
p004: Keep AGENTS.md as small router.

@EVIDENCE
e001: :https://hermes-agent.nousresearch.com/docs/user-guide/configuration
e002: :https://github.com/squoyster/dynovo-agent-rules/blob/main/AGENTS.md

@DECISIONS
d001: Keep normative execution rules separate from mutable ledgers.
d002: Use .axlr/.axls/.axlp/.axlt to remove ambiguity.
d003: Borrow append-only state mechanics and value sigils from Agent eXchange Language.

@RISKS
r001: HIGH | Smaller models may ignore symbolic rules unless notation block is loaded.
r002: MED | Markdown-first agents may wrap AXL in fences; state spec forbids it.
r003: MED | Too many overlays may recreate startup bloat.

